article.headline: Vermont 77, Albany 45
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) -- Alex Jensen scored 17 points and Scotty Jones had 16 and 10 rebounds as Vermont overwhelmed Albany 77-45 Thursday night. The Catamounts (19-7, 15-2 America East) kept pace with Boston University (16-1), who topped Stony Brook Thursday with one regular season game to play. Vermont won for the 15th time in the last 16 home games, 9-1 this season. Solid defense and nine points apiece by Jensen and Matt Hanson in the first half gave the Catamounts a 38-15 lead at the break. A 7-2 Albany run to start the second stanza brought the Great Danes to within 18 but Vermont, behind 10 second half points by Jones, rolled the rest of the way. Jensen went five-for-seven from three-point range en route to his 17 while Jones went eight-for-10 from the floor inside. T.J. Sorrentine had 14 points, a season-high eight rebounds and nine assists. Hanson finished with nine points and six rebounds while Matt Sheftic added eight points in his best outing of the season. The Catamounts are now 11-1 when holding opponents to 60 or fewer points this season and 16-1 when they out-rebound their foes.
